# Chatterino Wiki

This is the source code of the wiki hosted at https://wiki.chatterino.com

## Editing on Gitpod (simple)

Gitpod is a free online editor removing the need to install the development tools locally. You will need a __GitHub__ account to create a fork of this repository. You then open this fork in __Gitpod__ for editing and previewing. Then, you create a pull request on GitHub which the Chatterino developers will check and likely accept.

### First time setup (2 minutes)

1. [Fork this repository on GitHub](https://github.com/Chatterino/wiki/fork). This creates your own editable copy of the repository at `https://github.com/<yourusername>/wiki`.
1. Navigate to [gitpod.com](https://gitpod.com) and create a new workspace with the GitHub link __of your editable fork__.
1. Make sure that Gitpod has [the `public_repo` permission](https://gitpod.io/integrations) in the GitHub integration.

### Making changes and creating a Pull Request (1 minute + editing)

 1. Here, we create a Git branch for our changes, based on the current wiki (`origin/master`). Because of this, you will be able to create more branches for other pull requests in the future, always based on the current state of the Wiki.
 
    In Gitpod hit __F1__ and select "Create Branch From...". First, choose a name for your branch such as `fix-spelling-1`. Secondly, choose `origin/master` as the remote ref. Be sure to base it off of `origin/master` or else it might be out of date.

    ![example]( data:image/jpeg;base64,)
 

1. Switch to the `Explorer` tab in Gitpod. Edit the [Markdown](https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/) `.md` files in the `docs/` folder. Review your changes using the browser preview. If you closed the preview you can reopen it from the __Remote Explorer__ tab on the left. If you stopped the server, open the terminal (`F1` -> `Focus Terminal`) and enter `make`.

1. Now, __stage__ or __discard__ your changes in the __Source Control__ tab and then __commit__ them by entering a message and pressing Ctrl+Enter. You can repeat this and create multiple commits if you make multiple changes. Make sure to stage or discard all changes. Press __Publish Branch__ or __Sync__ to publish or update the branch. Alternatively you can choose "Push" in the Dropdown

    ![example](data:image/png;base64,)

1. [Create a Pull Request on the original Chatterino/wiki repository.](https://github.com/fourtf-burner/wiki/compare) Select your new branch on the right side.

    ![example](data:image/png;base64,)

1. Optional: If you dislike Gitpod keeping write and read access to your public GitHub repositories you can revoke access [here](https://github.com/settings/connections/applications/484069277e293e6d2a2a). You will then need to give it back when you want to make further edits.

## Running manually (advanced)

In case you want to try and run the wiki locally follow these steps (requires python 3):

- You can use `make serve` or if you want to use a virtual environment `make serve-venv`.

Or you can run these commands manually:

- _Optionally_ create and enter a virtual environment: `python3 -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate`
- Run `pip install -r requirements.txt`
- Run `mkdocs serve`
- Navigate to `localhost:8000` in your browser
